<p>I have svg circles, rotating by mousemove and need to rotate them by doubleclick/doubletap.</p>  <p>My function for rotate looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>function rotateCirc(id, coords) {     var parentN = $('#rus-circular');     var ctm = $('#'+id).parent().parent()[0].getScreenCTM();     var p = parentN[0].createSVGPoint();     p.x = coords[0];     p.y = coords[1];     p = p.matrixTransform(ctm.inverse());     var radians = Math.atan2(1990 - p.x, 1900 - p.y);     var degrees = (radians * (180 / Math.PI) * -1) + 90;     $('#'+id).css('transform','rotate('+degrees+'deg)'); } </code></pre>  <p>where <code>coords</code> is clientX and clientY click coordinates</p>  <p>But rotation work wrong, I need to rotate the "hole" of circle where i'm clicked;</p>  <p>How to rich there?</p>  <p><strong>My demo: <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/v2of73or/4/" rel="nofollow">http://jsfiddle.net/v2of73or/4/</a></strong></p>